(fifthQuint)Efficay of Extended Peginterferon Alpha 2a Treatment in HBeAg Negative Chronic Hepatitis B Patients.

 In this cohort study, the HBeAg negative chronic hepatitis B patients would be treated with peginterferon alpha 2a(PEG-IFN a-2a) for 96 week and followed 24 weeks after treatment.

 Serum HBV DNA load, HBsAg/anti-HBs level, HBeAg/anti-HBe will be tested at enrollment and every 3 months during treatment and follow period.

 Parameters of liver and kidney function, and liver ultrasound examination will be tested with intervals 1-3 months.

 The efficacies were evaluated by the rate of HBsAg loss during treatment and the rate of sustained viral response after treatment and follow up.

